==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Yelp
<hw>Yelp</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Yelped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Yelping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>yelpen</ets>,
<ets>⟦yogh⟧elpen</ets>, to boast, boast noisily, AS. <ets>gielpan</ets>,
<ets>gilpan</ets>, <ets>gylpan</ets>; akin to OHG. <ets>gelph</ets>
arrogant: cf. Icel. <ets>gj⟦amac⟧lpa</ets> to yelp. Cf.
<er>Yap</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To boast.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I keep [care] not of armes for to <qex>yelpe</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To utter a sharp, quick cry, as a hound; to bark
shrilly with eagerness, pain, or fear; to yaup.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A little herd of England's timorous deer,⟦br⟧
Mazed with a <qex>yelping</qex> kennel of French curs?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>At the least flourish of a broomstick or ladle, he would fly to
the door with a <qex>yelping</qex> precipitation.</q> <rj><qau>W.
Irving.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Yelp</ent>⟦br⟧

